WEBVTT

00:01:29.465 --> 00:01:31.606
These aren't isolated findings.

00:01:31.606 --> 00:01:34.945
On average, people tend to rate
themselves better than most

00:01:34.945 --> 00:01:42.095
in disciplines ranging from health,
leadership skills, ethics, and beyond.

00:01:42.095 --> 00:01:45.756
What's particularly interesting
is that those with the least ability

00:01:45.756 --> 00:01:50.636
are often the most likely to overrate
their skills to the greatest extent.

00:01:50.636 --> 00:01:53.367
People measurably poor 
at logical reasoning,

00:01:53.367 --> 00:01:54.070
grammar,

00:01:54.070 --> 00:01:55.117
financial knowledge,

00:01:55.117 --> 00:01:55.983
math,

00:01:55.983 --> 00:01:57.361
emotional intelligence,

00:01:57.361 --> 00:01:59.357
running medical lab tests,

00:01:59.357 --> 00:02:00.637
and chess